Ask HN: How do you research if a startup idea already exists?
text:
Hey there,

As, I assume a lot of people do, I have this endless Google Keep list of startup ideas that keeps getting longer and longer.

However, I'm a novice when it comes to finding the right terms to search if that idea already exists. I simply Google around with whatever feel relevant only to realise, months later, that there is a much better field-specific term or some vague jargon/synonym of what I was supposed to be searching for.

I assume this should be a somewhat elementary issue to vet startups and do competitor analysis.

How do you do that?

Also, what measures do you use to figure out the strength of the competing solutions?

Ask HN: Solo founders(Multiple projects)- How are you handling customer support?
text:
Hi there,

I have a 8-5 job that needs constant attention and I maintain a couple of services on the internet. I'm curious to know how, someone like me, is handling the customer support.

I receive an average of 15-20 user emails per day, 70% of them asking for the same information on the website FAQs. I reply to them with the templated responses. Is there a reliable tool to automate responses for such emails based on the questions? The remaining 30% are generic questions related to the provided service and some involve updating the subscriptions.
